      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The supported metadata attributes include In ChI, In ChIKey, SMILES, IUPAC chemical name, chemical formula, CAS number, and others... Besides querying external services, we also support converters to compute identifiers based on existing ones. For demonstration, we employed computation of molecular weight from SMILES using RDKit",
      "asbval:note": "Paper supports InChI, InChIKey, and formula as output metadata, and confirms local compute is possible, but only demonstrates molecular weight computation. InChI/InChIKey generation via RDKit is not explicitly documented in passages.",
