    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/converter-pipeline-integration-and-execution/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The software package MSMeta Enhancer is a tool to enhance the metadata content of records in mass spectral library files. It takes as input a single .msp file with multiple mass spectra records and a list of annotation steps... The supported metadata attributes include In ChI, In ChIKey, SMILES, IUPAC chemical name, chemical formula, CAS number, and others... Multiple databases and services are included, currently supporting the chemical identifier resolver (CIR), chemical translation service (CTS)... Integrated Database for Small Molecules (IDSM)... Pub Chem... and Bridge Db... Additionally, instead of querying external databases, computing the identifiers is also supported (e.g. molecular weight from SMILES)... run asynchronous annotation of spectra data asyncio.run(app.annotate_spectra(services, jobs))",
      "asbval:note": "All major components verified: services (CIR, CTS, PubChem, IDSM, BridgeDb), metadata fields (SMILES, InChI, CAS, formula, InChIKey, IUPAC name), asynchronous execution, .msp file input, and Application instance usage.",
