    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dynamic-method-signature-introspection/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The tool processes the spectral library by iteratively executing all steps for each entry until no new metadata is found... The supported metadata attributes include In ChI, In ChIKey, SMILES, IUPAC chemical name, chemical formula, CAS number, and others. The particular available conversions can be found in the documentation via https://msmetaenhancer.readthedocs.io/ and are open to extension.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes MSMetaEnhancer as supporting conversion between metadata attributes and querying external services, but does not explicitly discuss dynamic introspection of converter objects, reflection-based signature validation, or Job enumeration. The paper focuses on the user-facing annotation workflow and supported conversions, not the internal converter discovery mechanism.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-04494",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
