    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/smiles-inchi-round-trip-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Besides querying external services, we also support converters to compute identifiers based on existing ones. For demonstration, we employed computation of molecular weight from SMILES using RDKit (Landrum et al., 2022).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms RDKit is used for local SMILES-based computation (molecular weight derivation), but does not explicitly mention Chem.MolFromSmiles, Chem.inchi.MolToInchi, or canonical SMILES export functions. The specific API calls and round-trip validation workflow are not documented in the passages.",
