    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/structured-logging-and-metric-extraction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To improve the usability of the tool, a Galaxy (Afgan et al., 2018) wrapper was created to provide a user-friendly interface and a simple way of reproducible data processing and analysis... Any issues regarding the annotation process (such as the absence of target data or unavailability of a service) are recorded in a detailed log file, which can be specified as an optional output of the tool.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that MSMetaEnhancer records issues in a detailed log file as optional output, and uses asynchronous annotation. However, the paper does NOT explicitly describe parsing logs to compute fill-rate statistics or coverage metrics (before/after metadata completeness). The logging capability exists but the specific analytics workflow (fill-rate computation, per-attribute tracking) is not documented in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-04494",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
