      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The tool processes the spectral library by iteratively executing all steps for each entry until no new metadata is found... Since it takes some non-trivial time for the services to respond to a query, this task is suitable for the asynchronous approach, making the tool computationally efficient... Any issues regarding the annotation process (such as the absence of target data or unavailability of a service) are recorded in a detailed log file, which can be specified as an optional output of the tool.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms asynchronous service calls and logging of issues/unavailability, but does NOT describe a dedicated health-monitoring system that tracks uptime, error counts, latency, or produces aggregated health-status reports. The paper only mentions that issues are recorded in a log file. The card's claim of a monitoring framework with health-status reports is not supported by the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-21105-joss-04494",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
